-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Candente, Maple, Pomalca, Rio Cristal
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2011-12-28T21:26:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/peru-stocks-buenaventura-candente-maple-pomalca-rio-cristal.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.7 percent to 19,268.55. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index  slid 1.5 percent to 2,478.65.  Mining and industrial stocks slumped after commodities
declined in  New York  and  London , said  Daniel Romero , an analyst
at Lima-based investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian
exploration company, fell 10 percent to 9 cents.  Candente Copper
Corp. (DNT)  , the Canadian mining exploration company with
operations in Peru, dropped 6.1 percent to 93 cents.  Empresa
Agroindustrial Pomalca SA  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar producer, slid
4 percent to 48 centimos after futures declined in New York.
 Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN)  , the countryâ€™s biggest
precious-metals miner, fell 3.2 percent to $37.75 after
opponents to its Minas Conga gold project said they plan
protests Jan. 2.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural
gas producer with operations in Peru, dropped 1.8 percent to
$1.08 after crude declined in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
